x4freetext: -A SYSTEMATIC INVESTIGATION OF (N,T) REACTIONS AT 14 TO
15 MEV ON MEDIUM AND HEAVY MASS NUCLEI.-
80 PERCENT OF NEUTRONS HAVE AN ENERGY OF 14.7 +- 0.3
MEV FOR THIN SAMPLE (S32,CA40,GE70,Y89 AND LA139).
HOWEVER, FOR MEASUREMENTS ON CR50, FE54, ZN64, MO92
AND AU197, DUE TO THE SAMPLE THICKNESS, THE MEAN
ENERGY OF NEUTRONS WAS AROUND 14.6 +- 0.4 MEV.
HIGH PURITY TARGET IN POWDER FORM.
UNIT EMPLOYING TWO 12.5 * 7.5 CM NAI(TL) CRYSTALS.
GE(LI) DETECTOR, 28 CM3, CONNECTED TO A 4000
THE ERRORS GIVEN ARE MAXIMUM ERRORS AND INCLUDE ALL
ERRORS EXCEPT THOSE FROM UNCERTAINTIES IN DECAY SCHEME
